From: conda-forge
Subject: [PATCH] Use ghc-pkg register directly instead of cabal register for Stage0

When using a different bootstrap GHC version (e.g., 9.6.7 to build 9.2.8),
Cabal's register command doesn't properly register packages to the Stage0
package database.

The issue:
1. cabal copy --target-package-db creates the .conf file in the right place
2. cabal register (without --package-db support) may register to wrong db
3. Subsequent configure steps can't find the newly registered package

The fix uses ghc-pkg register directly for Stage0 packages, similar to how
copyConf handles bootstrap packages. This is more reliable than going through
Cabal's registration machinery.

diff --git a/hadrian/src/Rules/Register.hs b/hadrian/src/Rules/Register.hs
--- a/hadrian/src/Rules/Register.hs
+++ b/hadrian/src/Rules/Register.hs
@@ -141,9 +141,28 @@ buildConf _ context@Context {..} _conf = do
         when (bignum == "gmp") $
             need [path -/- "include/ghc-gmp.h"]
 
     -- Copy and register the package.
+    -- Note: For Stage0 with different bootstrap versions, Cabal.registerPackage
+    -- doesn't reliably register to the correct package database. We use ghc-pkg
+    -- directly instead, similar to how copyConf handles bootstrap packages.
     Cabal.copyPackage context
-    Cabal.registerPackage context
+
+    case stage of
+        Stage0 -> do
+            -- Use ghc-pkg register directly for Stage0
+            -- The .conf file was created by copyPackage
+            pkgDbPath <- packageDbPath stage
+            pkgId <- pkgIdentifier package
+            let confFile = pkgDbPath -/- pkgId <.> "conf"
+            putProgressInfo $ "| Register package " ++ quote (pkgName package) ++ " (via ghc-pkg)"
+            -- Call ghc-pkg register directly with the conf file
+            ghcPkgPath <- builderPath (GhcPkg Init stage)
+            verbosity <- getVerbosity
+            let verbosityFlag = if verbosity < Chatty then ["-v0"] else []
+            cmd_ [ghcPkgPath] (["--no-user-package-db", "--global-package-db", pkgDbPath
+                              , "register"] ++ verbosityFlag ++ [confFile])
+        _ ->
+            Cabal.registerPackage context
 
     -- We declare that this rule also produces files matching:
     --   - <root>/stage<N>/lib/<arch>-<os>-ghc-<version>/*libHS<pkgid>*
